cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.AI, cs.SE, cs.SI 

This paper discusses the use of Cyber Threat Intelligence (CTI) to improve the security of Software Defined Networks (SDN), which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and network security (cs.NI). The paper also mentions the incorporation of intelligence to face new attacks, which could be related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of a physical testbed to analyze how malicious traffic could be blocked suggests a focus on software engineering (cs.SE) and system integration (cs.SI).
